eva-orchestrator

context: After deep discussion about dual-use AI risks and Five Eyes complexity, Marco Presta decided to focus EVA exclusively on serving Canada and Canadians. Removed Five Eyes expansion. Focus: bilingualism (en-CA/fr-CA), WCAG 2.1 AA+, PIPEDA compliance, Indigenous protocols, world-class quality.
quote: wow.. mark this moment in the logs. yes, lets build it for Canada and Canadians
impact: Reduced scope from 471M (Five Eyes) to 38M (Canada). Eliminated weaponization risks, jurisdictional conflicts, multi-nation compliance costs. Positioned EVA as Canadian leadership example for world to follow.
commitment: Build world's best AI governance platform for Canada. If it's good enough for Canadians, it's good enough for anyone.

rationale: Hash chains + immutable storage (Azure Blob legal hold) provide tamper-evident guarantees GC requires. Blockchain properties needed: append-only logs, cryptographic integrity, tamper detection. Blockchain properties NOT needed: decentralization, multi-party consensus, external verification (single department deployment).
context: After joint analysis by Senior Advisor (ChatGPT) and Scrum Master (Copilot), decision made to use hash-chain audit pattern instead of blockchain. EVA has trusted operator (AICOE+IITB), central governance. Blockchain adds cost (gas fees), latency (seconds vs <100ms), complexity (nodes/consensus) without solving multi-party trust problem EVA doesn't have.
revisitIf: EVA expands to 5+ departments (multi-party trust needed) OR Auditor General requires external verification OR international partnerships require decentralized governance (post Canada-first)
decision: Blockchain DECLINED - Hash-Chain Audit Pattern Selected
alternative: EVA Ledger Pattern: (1) Hash-linked audit tables with previous_hash + current_hash = SHA-256(previous + payload + timestamp), (2) Merkle snapshots to Key Vault (hourly/daily), (3) Immutable storage with legal hold, (4) Chain integrity verification on read.
decidedBy: Marco Presta (Product Owner) + Senior Advisor (ChatGPT) + Scrum Master (Copilot)
